    {
      "text": "NBA Fastbreak '98 is a basketball simulator released for the Sony PlayStation in 1997. It takes place during the 1997-98 National Basketball Association season. It was published by Midway Games and GT Interactive. Originally announced under the title \"Hardwood Heroes\", the game was released with minimal changes as NBA Action 98 on Sega Saturn and Microsoft Windows, published by Sega, with Kobe Bryant of the Los Angeles Lakers as the cover athlete. Another version was being developed by Z-Axis for the Nintendo 64 under the title \"NBA Fast Break 64\", with a prospective November 1997 release, but it was cancelled.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    }
